               <scopecontent id="aspace_eb6aff46fad6082565b9019e8ca249a7">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Full Title: S'ensuivent plusieurs cantiques, ou noels composes les annees 1610, et 1611, Et premierement son faict en dialogue de l'ange, et du Pecheur parlant en la personne de tous Qui se chante a l'air de nova estantione trois basanets et. [Signed: Raymond] f.1-3r [verso blank] - Exorcismus mirabilis efficacia pro his, qui in matrimonio a daemonibus, vel maleficis diabolica arte impediuntur, seu maleficiantur Rubrica. f.4-12r [verso blank] - Poeme de la glorieuse mort, et passion de nostre sauveur, et redempteur Jesus Christ. Autre sur le mesme subiect... [Signed: Raymondus Curio Parr[ochi]ae S[anc]tj Stephani. f.13-21. [Followed by additional carols and poems, written by the same author between 1610 and 1634] MS, probably in the author's hand. [No place, 1610-1634] 1-29, 29 bis, 30-42 leaves numbered in a later hand. 29 cm.; Lettered on spine: Raymond. Noels. <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>and</part>
                     </title> Noels. France.; Half-leather with tan marbled boards.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
